		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />FCEUX's sound.cpp implements the &quot;Lookup table&quot; model, summing 3*tri+2*noise*dpcm and running that through a table called <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">wlookup2</tt>. I tried compensating for it (and fixing the erroneous write that failed to disable NMI), and everything cleared up in FCEUX. I'll try it later on my NES.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
