		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Did an orginal, unmodded Famicom sound like this? (Sampl</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It will probably still be audibly aliased because the Nyquist rate of 13,160 Hz is below the identifiable limit of human hearing, 16KHz. As far as I can tell, approaching the Nyquist limit with rectangular transitions between samples appears to produce aliasing at any rate.<br /><br />The routine could be sped up considerably at a cost of ROM size by precomputing a logarithmic scale for one octave, and playing it back at multiple octave rates.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


